    "media:imagetext": "® IONA AIRLINES\nWith its 118-passenger Boeing 737, Aloha Airlines introduces the biggest and\nroomiest aircraft in the history of inter-island travel. The cabin width and overhead\nspace of the flower power \"FUNBIRD\" are the same as on intercontinental jets,\noffering every passenger more jet comfort.\nThe gay \"FUNBIRD\" design has been carried throughout the corporate image\nwhich includes \"partypants\" outfits for stewardesses, matching ground hostess\nuniforms, Aloha shirts for counter agents and customer employees.\n201\n0055",
